DEFINITIONS:

"Software" - for this document, Software is defined as: the combination of text
and other characters comprising the content, saved in one or more files, which
describes sequences of specific actions to be performed by the computer.
Software comprises all such files which are required to create, either directly
or indirectly, an executable computer program. In addition, Software comprises
any text and image based documentation related to the technical nature of the
Software.

"Artwork" - any creative or artistic work that does not meet the above definition
of Software, and is saved as files in a format for storing text, images, audio,
or related data which is in support of processing these formats by the Software.

